!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

pretty /ˈprɪtɪ/

(prettier,prettiest) 

1. ADJ If you describe someone, especially a girl, as pretty , you mean that they look nice and are attractive in a delicate way. (尤指女孩) 漂亮的 

例： She's a very charming and very pretty girl. 她是一个非常迷人、非常漂亮的姑娘。 

2. prettily ADV 漂亮地 

例： She smiled again, prettily. 她又笑了，很美。 

3. ADJ A place or a thing that is pretty is attractive and pleasant, in a charming but not particularly unusual way. (某地、某物) 漂亮的 

例： ...a very pretty little town. …一座非常漂亮的小镇。 

4. prettily ADV 漂亮地 

例： The living-room was prettily decorated. 客厅装饰得很漂亮。 

5. ADV You can use pretty before an adjective or adverb to slightly lessen its force. 颇 [非正式] [ADV adj/adv] 

例： I had a pretty good idea what she was going to do. 我颇清楚她打算做什么。

</div>

